 Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">M.A.G </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">UK’s </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">second </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">largest airport operator and owns and </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">operates</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> Manchester, </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Stanste</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">d, </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">East </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Midlands and Bournemouth airports.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">M.A.G</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> airports handle</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> over 42</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> million passengers and </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">600</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">,000 tonnes of cargo, </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">he group’s activities cover air traffic services, car parking, retail concession management, airport security services, fire fighting, e</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">ngineering and property development. </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">M.A.G</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> owned by the ten local authorities of Greater Manchester</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">, in partnership with global investment manager IFM.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:-0.05pt">Our responses to the questions in the Call for Evidence are set out below.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.31pt; padding-left:21.69pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Questions</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">resilient are the UK’s transport networks (including road, rail and air) to adverse winter weather?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">M.A.G airports have taken steps to ensure that, as far as possible, flights can continue operating safely during periods of snowfall. </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">All M.A.G</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> airports ha</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">ve a comprehensive Winter Operations Plan, </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">which comes into effect on 1 November </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">following consultation with airfield tenants. The plan explains what preparations have been made to deal with extreme winter weather, and sets out roles and responsibilities.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">It also </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">includes a detailed set of crisis management plans in the event of severe disruption</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Stansted Airport’s plan is subject to rigorous testing programmes, including summer desktop exercise run jointly with airlines, handling agents and operational t</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">eams. A Terminal Welfare Plan, also operated in conjunction with airlines, sets out roles and responsibilities for passenger information, provisions, facilities and hotels and rebooking.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">The Winter Operations Plan is reviewed annually and</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> improvements added based on lessons learned</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">For example, </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">the Terminal team at Manchester have carried out additional work this year to make the passenger welfare element more robust. This included working with procurement colleagues to look at how to sec</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">ure additional supplies at short notice; working with Manchester City Council to pool resources; reviewing communications, such as use of passenger information screens; and working closely with retail colleagues to ensure the availability of food, drink an</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">d essentials.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Our terminal and operations teams also draw on best practice from other European airports.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Work is </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">underway at Manchester to explore how to ensure the safety and well-being of colleagues, but looking at how they can get into work, e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">advance booking of hotels for operation critical colleagues and call out groups for those living close by.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What lessons have been learned since the severe weather experienced in the winter of 2009-10? What practical changes have been made to ensure the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">is now better equipped to deal with severe weather?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">M.A.G airports have invested substantially in snow clearing equipment since the severe 2009-10 winter (see below for details). Lessons learned included increased supplies of and storage areas for road sal</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">t and de-icer; improvements to crisis management systems and changes to weather forecasting information, to allow for more accurate forecasting.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Despite extensive preparation and investment</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">, constant snowfall remains a significant challenge. Just 3mm of snow on the ground sees airfield operations slow down and constant snowfall makes any clearing operation </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">prolonged and challenging</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> Manchester Airport has invested in equipment to monitor the</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> ground temperature (snow will melt if the ground is warmer than freezing) which means that </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">appropriate airfield anti</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">-icing </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">action</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> can be </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">undertaken</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">in a timely and efficient manner, thus preserving operational continuity.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How well prepared are the Governm</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ent, local authorities and transport providers for adverse winter weather? What more should be done to ensure a coordinated response?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">We have observed that during periods of bad weather improvements do appear to have been made to procedures for major roads</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> (motorways and trunk roads) to keep them clear, though some problems continue on A and B roads, impacting on airport colleagues getting to and from work. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffff00; font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">East Midlands Airport</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> is a member of the LRF Severe Weather Group which coordinates the response to inclement weather </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">across the County. </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">All main roads leading to </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Bournemouth</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> Airport </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">re gritted and maintained by </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">the C</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">ounty Council and </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">details of the various routes covered are</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> available on their website</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="color:#1f497d; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">At Stansted, all private roads and car parks within the airport boundary are gritted, maintained and managed by Stansted Airport Limited, all other primary and secondary roads are managed by Essex County Council and in the cas</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">e of the M11, the Highways Agency.</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> Stansted Airport works in partnership with Local Authorities, Government Agencies and surface access providers through the airport’s Transport Forum to ensure all necessary steps are taken to prepare for and manage incid</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">ences of inclement weather. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">2.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Manchester Airport has a good working relationship with Manchester City Council, who are responsible for gritting the main access roads to the site. Onsite roads</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> and pavements are looked after by Manchester Airport’s landside </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">team, who pre-treat the area in advance of anticipated snowfall.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.31pt; padding-left:21.69pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Winter readiness</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> at M.A.G airports</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">: Some key statistics</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Manchester Airport</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:11.24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Manchester Airport has 37 different pieces of airfield snow clearing kit, ranging from tractor unit snowploughs to the huge snow blowers used by Canadian airports.  </span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">We spent over £2 million upgrading this fleet between 2009 and 201</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">0, and continue to invest</span><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt"> in upgrades to our fleet year on year.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:11.24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">We have more than doubled the amount of onsite storage capacity for anti-icing fluid from 160,000 litres to 400,000 litres. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:11.24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt">Snow clearing teams are on standby 24/7 between November and March.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Stansted Airport</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Futura Lt BT'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:11.24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'